The following uses Math.PI to create a String representation of the Double PI. We then determine where the decimal is at in that string using String#indexOf. We then request the number of decimals we would like to see using Scanner. Assuming the input is a non-negative integer we attempt to find the substring of the String PI using the initial index of &quot;.&quot; and the remaining numbers.

```java

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        requestInput();
